<TITLE> Rubel admits double murder </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 1 (bdnews24.com)  Rubel confessed to a double murder in Gulshan, where he shot dead a businessman and his wife. He gave the testimony at the court of Dhaka Metropolitan Magistrate Zulfikar Hayat under Section 164 in the afternoon, deputy sub inspector Khandaker Ekhlasur Rahman, General Recording Officer, told bdnews24.com. Rubel was later sent to jail, he added. The suspected killers 'Rubel' and his associate 'Mithun' were arrested in Jhalakati early Sunday. They are the prime suspects in the murder of a couple in the capital's Gulshan area last week. Rubel also confessed to the killings in front of reporters. Businessman Sadikur Rahman and wife Romana Nargis were shot dead at their Kalachandpur home in Gulshan on Mar 24. Ekhlasur Rahman said Rubel described the incident in his testimony. Meanwhile, metropolitan magistrate Rokhsana Begum Happy granted the police three days to further interrogate Rubel. Police earlier was granted three days to quiz him on Tuesday. bdnew
